Submodules

endemo2.endemo module

class Endemo[source]

Bases: object

This is the whole program. From here we control what the model does on the highest level.

Variables:

  • input_manager (Input) – holds all the processed input_and_settings from the Excel sheets for the current run of the program.

  • countries_in_group (dict[str, Country]) – holds all the country objects, accessible by the countries_in_group english name.

  • preprocessor (Preprocessor) – holds an additional layer of preprocessed data, building upon the input_manager.

create_instance()[source]

Creates an instance of the model.

execute_with_preprocessing()[source]

Executes the whole program from start to end.

execute_without_preprocessing()[source]

Executes only the model with the updated settings. Builds upon, but does not recalculate preprocessing.

update_settings()[source]

Rereads the instance settings.

write_all_output()[source]

Writes the whole output to the output folder.

write_model_output()[source]

Writes all the output that comes from the model instance.

write_preprocessing_output()[source]

Writes all the output that comes from preprocessing.
